An ordinance of the Lords and Commons in Parliament assembled Prohibiting the importation of whale-oyle, fins, or gils, but by ships set forth from hence, and by English subjects. Die Martis 6. Maii. 1645. England and Wales. Parliament.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
printed for John Wright at the Kings Head in the Old Bayley, London : 7. May. 1645.
A variant of the edition without "7. May." in the imprint. Order to print signed: Joh. Brown Cler. Parliamentorum. Annotation on Thomason copy: the "7" in the imprint date has been altered to "8". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
